.el .ds Aq '
.TH DELPHI-PALETTE 1  "delphitools-cli 0.1.0" "delphitools manual"
.SH NAME
palette \- Generate colour palettes using 28 strategies across 6 categories
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpalette\fR [\fB\-\-strategy\fR] [\fB\-\-size\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-lock\fR] [\fB\-\-seed\fR] [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-pretty\fR] [\fB\-\-list\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate colour palettes using 28 strategies across 6 categories
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-strategy\fR \fI<STRATEGY>\fR
Strategy name (e.g. analogous, 80s, ocean\-sunset). Omit to list strategies
.TP
\fB\-\-size\fR \fI<SIZE>\fR [default: 5]
Number of colours (default 5)
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: hex]
Output format: hex (default), css, json, png
.TP
\fB\-\-lock\fR \fI<LOCK>\fR
Lock specific slots, comma\-separated: "0:#ff6600,3:#003366"
.TP
\fB\-\-seed\fR \fI<SEED>\fR
Seed for reproducible output (any 64\-bit unsigned integer)
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-pretty\fR
Prefix each colour with its slot index (e.g. `[0]`) — useful for `\-\-lock`
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
List all available strategies and exit
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
